headline: ‘Ingrained’ Review: The Wisdom in Wood
summary: Callum Robinson, a highly skilled Scottish furniture maker, has a boot in both camps.  In “Ingrained,” a wry, wise and deeply felt memoir, Mr. Robinson reminds us that trees were the original domiciles for our distant ancestors—providing a relatively safe place “where everything didn’t want so very badly to eat us.”
